x4freetext: English Translation of AE 14 264
Radiative Capture Cross Sections of Tellurium Isotope
As a Function of Neutron Energies Up to 1.5 KeV
Kurchatov Institute Linear Electron Accelerato
.Neutrons Produced from a Uranium Target of the Linear
Accelerator Surrounded by a 4 Cm Water Moderator.  Th
Neutron Pulse Length was Either 0.9 or 0.6 Microsec
.Absolute Measurements
Time of Flight
Sodium-Iodide Scintillation Crystal Detectors
For Neutron Flux Monitoring
.Corrections were Made For Doppler Broadening, Multipl
Scattering, and Self-Shielding
.Discussion was Given For the Background Countribution
And Errors of the Cross Sections.  The Basic
Uncertainties Which Contribute to the Error in the
Value of ((52-TE-A(N,G),,SIG)*(52-TE-A(N,TOT),,WID))
Max Statistical Error in the Sum of the Coun-
Ting Rates For the Test Sample Amounting to 2 to 5
Per-Cent  Up to 10 Per-Cent at Weak Resonances
Max Error in the Sample Thickness of the Orde
Of 2-3 Per-Cent  Mainly from Oxidation of Tellurium
Change in Counting Efficiency Among Resonances
Of 5 Per-Cent
Max  Error in the Correction Factor For
Counted Scattered Neutrons of a Maximum 4 Per-Cent
Max  Error Due to Multiple Scattering
Up to 3 Per-Cent
Error in the Counting Rate of the Black Sample
At Resonance - 2 Per-Cent
Error of Determination of the Neutron Spectrum
Of 2 Per-Cent
Max  Extrapolation Error of Sig-G-Res Times
Tot-Wid - 2 to 5 Per-Cent
